The paper discusses the development of neuromorphic chips, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of spin-torque nano-oscillators also involves the study of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET) and electromagnetism (cs.EM). The paper also discusses the implementation of cognitive tasks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and the study of embedded systems (cs.ES).
